'He was running a great team,' Schnuelle added.

Sass, owner and founder of Wild and Free Mushing, has been racing and training huskies for 12 years. 

Originally from Excelsior, Minnesota, Sass moved to Alaska in 1998 to 'fulfill a lifelong dream' of living in the state.

He attended the University of Alaska Fairbanks where he graduated with a major in geography and started mushing shortly after. 

